{
  "stem": "7860.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I used to go around begging.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were many professional entertainers on the train, from opera singers and musicians entertain the black marketeers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And as I was going around begging-- as I go around begging, they only gave me two potatoes-- the farmer, the peasant-- or a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And a man can't live by bread alone.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I would go into business, because there were many boys and men selling candy, charms, cigarettes, in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Several years later, it wouldn't have been allowed to be sold on trains.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I wanted to go into business myself selling candy charms.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I needed money.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had no money.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so I composed my song for myself, which was song composed was that the black marketeers are coming to the peasants and giving all their valuables to the peasant, while the peasant is stuffing his mattress full of money instead of with straw and wearing galoshes with white gloves, throwing out manure with the white gloves.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the gendarmes are liquidating the stuff from the-- from the black marketeers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when I sang the songs on the train-- with somebody else's melody, of course, and I passed my hat, and I collected enough money, it took me about a week not to eat to save enough money, collect enough.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I followed some boys to the candy factory.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And many times, I followed them straight home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't know where they were going after the day is over.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I finally found a candy factory in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I found another candy factory outside of Warsaw, candy which in skinnier.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I started selling candy charms on the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
